	<h1>Storing Page Data</h1>
	<div class = "row-fluid">
		<div class="span8 offset2">
			<div class = "well">
				<p>
					All page data is store in .page files, which are very simple data containers.  There are no real "rules" associated with them, they represent a set of key -> value attributes.  Each .page file is compiled and passed into a Jinja template.
				</p>
				
			</div>
			<h3>An example .page file:</h3>
			<pre>
 :html-title: Html title
 :heading: Page Heading
 :title: Nav Title
 :home_page: Display on the home page?
 :template: Non Default Template
 :order: Order in nav bar
 :meta-description:
 :meta-keywords:
 :styles:
	Style specific to this page
 :scripts:
	Scripts specific to this page
 :content:
	The main content
		</pre>
			<div class = "alert alert-danger" style = "text-align: center; font-weight: bold">
				These are the values that I have chosen to include, none of them are required! 
			</div>

		<h3>Rules and Special Attributes:</h3>
			<ul>
				<li>If a line begins with <b>:anystring:</b> it will be considered the name of an attribute</li>
				<li><b>:homepage:</b> determines if this page will appear in the navigation bar (name to be changed)</li>
				<li><b>:order:</b> Defines the order that this page will be appear in the navigation list.</li>
			</ul>
		</div>
	</div>